defaultWe believe a new Land Agency body is required to champion and promote the Land Reform Act and the wider Lan
defaultd Reform agenda. This Land Agency would assist and advise communities on the registration and acquisition processes, work with community bodies and land owners to manage negotiations and facilitate transfers, and advise ministers on issues of public intere
defaultst and sustainable development.
