defaultACF’s application to buy 
defaultthe for
defaultest 
defaultto de
defaultliver a wide range of economic, social and environmental benefits 
defaultwas approved in December 2009
default, but their attempts to raise the necessary funding have been repeatedly thwarted, most recently on the grounds of state aid and concerns over “market d
defaultistortion”. ACF are one of a number of community organisations with approved NFLS applications who are unable to progress until this issue is resolved.
default&#xa0;default(v) Interaction between public funding for the community sector and other public fundingdefault/ 
defaultincentive defaultmechanismsdefault. 
defaultFunding bodies, particularly if operating either side of the Scottish border, do not appear to prioritise that State Aid compatibility runs across their respective programmes. This has been particularly problematic in the field of renewable en
defaultergy in relation to the UK Government’s Feed in Tariff, which was declared a State Aid (even though a parallel mechanism, the 
defaultRenewables
default Obligation, was not) and automatically incompatible with any form of public funding for ‘purchase and installation cost
defaults' of energy generating plant. Uncertainty around the basis of the State Aid decision, and the interpretation of ‘purchase and installation costs' has delayed a number of community projects and led to a loss of public (including UK Government) funding whic
defaulth has inhibited the development of individual projects and the sector as a whole. For example, the Isle of 
defaultGigha
default Heritage Trust lost a grant offer of over £250,000 from the ERDF.
