default(vii) There is no recourse to a formal appeals process. defaultWithin the UK there isn't an independent appeals process for State Aid decision
defaults, and obtaining an opinion from the European Commission is practically impossible for small projects (and would in any case need to involve the national State Aid teams that would have made the decision in the first place).
default&#xa0;defaultGovernment ActionsdefaultThere is no
default single solution the state aid problem, however there are a number of straightforward actions which the Government can undertake which would greatly mitigate its impact on the community sector
default&#xa0;
default(defaultidefault) defaultImproved appraisal of state aid defaultGovernment should set a 
defaultpositive tone, making it clear that state aid should not been seen as an insurmountable barrier or a pretext for refusal, and should also ensure that all those charged with state aid appraisal are appropriately trained and supported to do so.
defaultCivil servant
defaults and local government officers
default need to be empowered to make 
defaultappropriate 
defaultappraisals
default of projects based on a thorough understanding of the regulations and a realistic view of the likelihood of challenge.
default&#xa0;
default(ii) defaultDevelop defaultapproved schemes fodefaultr community based defaultactdefaultivitydefaultA more thorough-going solution is to develop approved schemes for the activities of community based, non-profit distributing organisations, and to ensure that where possible they are covered by General Block Exemptions. 
defaultDesign and notification of ap
defaultproved schemes would have to be taken forward on a sector-by-sector basis, and it is unlikely that they could ever provide total coverage, however they would greatly improve the situation.
default 
defaultSuch schemes are part of the normal support infrastructure for alm
defaultost all commercial business sectors; without similar support the community sector will never develop to any significant scale.
default&#xa0;
default(iii) defaultAccess to an appeals processdefaultIt would be beneficial to establish an independent (non-governmental) ombudsman for State Aid
default, with responsibility for managing an independent appeals process. This would also give comfort to those who administer the system and promote a more confident approach within the sector.
